            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin", style="text-align: justify;">
                  1. 5 - ounces fresh or frozen skinless salmon fillets <br>
                  2. 12 ounces sweet potatoes, scrubbed and cut crosswise into 1/8- to 1/4-inch-thick slices <br>
                  3. 2 teaspoons canola oil <br>
                  4. 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano, crushed <br>
                  5. 1/2 teaspoon ground ancho chile pepper or chili powder <br>
                  6. 1/2 teaspoon ground cumin <br>
                  7. 1/4 teaspoon salt<br>
                  8. 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper <br>
                  9. 1 medium orange, peeled and coarsely chopped  <br>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row details no-margin">
                <div class="col-xs-12 no-margin" style="text-align: justify;">
                  <b>Direction</b><br>
                  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.<br>
                  2. Thaw fish, if frozen. Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels; set aside.<br>
                  3. In a medium bowl, toss sweet potato slices with oil. <br>
                  4. In a small bowl, combine oregano, chile pepper, cumin, salt, and black pepper. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of the oregano mixture evenly on the salmon. Add remaining oregano mixture to sweet potatoes and toss to coat. <br>
                  5. Tear off four 18-inch squares of heavy foil. Lightly coat one side of each foil square with nonstick cooking spray. <br>
                  6. In the center of each foil square, arrange one-fourth of the sweet potato slices, overlapping slightly. <br>
                  7. Top each sweet potato mound with a salmon fillet and arrange orange pieces atop salmon. <br>
                  8. For each packet, bring up two opposite edges of a foil square and seal with a double fold. <br>
                  9. Fold ends to completely enclose fish and vegetables, leaving space for steam to build. <br>
                  10.Place the packets, seam sides up, on a very large baking sheet.<br>
                  11.Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork and sweet potatoes are tender.<br>
                  12.Open the packets carefully when checking doneness. Transfer contents of each packet to a plate.





